03:20.240 --> 03:22.500
So,have you thought
about your mother's offer?

03:22.510 --> 03:24.870
Yeah,I have.

03:25.110 --> 03:27.220
I've got one question.

03:27.420 --> 03:29.290
Why June?

03:29.320 --> 03:31.360
What's wrong with
getting married in July?

03:31.390 --> 03:33.710
Or the following October?

03:34.570 --> 03:37.060
October is a perfectly good month.

03:37.090 --> 03:41.100
Birds all fly south,so you don't
have to worry about swan attacks.

03:42.560 --> 03:45.430
Charlie,if you don't want to get
married in June,we don't have to.

03:45.440 --> 03:46.150
What? No,no.

03:46.160 --> 03:48.540
No,that's not what I'm saying at all.

03:48.550 --> 03:50.920
Where do you get this stuff?

03:53.180 --> 03:53.920
So?

03:53.930 --> 03:55.620
So,what?

03:55.630 --> 03:58.340
Do you want to get married in June?

03:58.350 --> 04:00.290
Oh,we're back on that.

04:03.290 --> 04:07.500
Well,I can't think of
any good reason why not.

04:07.530 --> 04:09.680
And believe me,I'm trying.

04:10.110 --> 04:11.630
So that's it?

04:11.660 --> 04:15.190
We're getting married June
26 at the Bel Air Hotel?

04:15.830 --> 04:17.209
I guess so.

04:17.260 --> 04:19.570
Oh,Charlie,I'm so happy.

04:19.600 --> 04:23.230
That's only because you don't have
a swan beak in your eye socket yet.

04:24.800 --> 04:27.850
I'm going to go call your mom,and
then my mom and then all my friends.

04:27.890 --> 04:29.490
Good,good.

04:29.580 --> 04:30.620
Alan,we're going to do it.

04:30.650 --> 04:32.480
June 26 at the Bel Air Hotel.

04:32.510 --> 04:34.250
Oh,my God! Oh,my God! Oh,my God!

04:34.290 --> 04:36.370
That's so wonderful!

04:36.450 --> 04:38.680
I know! I gotta go call everybody.

04:40.990 --> 04:43.190
Congratulations.

04:43.960 --> 04:44.680
Thanks.

04:44.730 --> 04:47.370
Wow,the end of an era.

04:48.430 --> 04:49.210
Guess so.

04:49.220 --> 04:51.120
Well,you had a good run.

04:52.910 --> 04:53.790
Yep.

04:53.800 --> 04:55.850
But now it's over.

04:56.580 --> 04:58.460
Forever.

05:00.490 --> 05:02.980
Nothing's going to change,Alan.

05:03.000 --> 05:07.280
Sure,I'm going to be married,but I'm still going to be
the same guy living in the same house with the same woman.

05:07.290 --> 05:09.750
Yes,yes,the same woman.

05:09.870 --> 05:12.050
Forever.

05:13.550 --> 05:15.410
Hey,can I be the best man?

05:15.420 --> 05:17.340
You'll need a sex change.

05:19.500 --> 05:20.690
Where you going?

05:20.700 --> 05:22.200
Out for a drink.

05:22.210 --> 05:23.250
You can drink here.

05:23.260 --> 05:25.900
I could,but I don't want to vomit here.

05:26.280 --> 05:28.520
Wait,wait,wait,I'll go with you.

05:28.680 --> 05:29.300
Why?

05:29.350 --> 05:31.370
I'm not done poking at you.

05:31.970 --> 05:34.370
Hey,shouldn't you ask the
ol' ball and chain first?

05:34.420 --> 05:35.630
I don't need her permission.

05:35.660 --> 05:36.500
Really?

05:36.510 --> 05:38.770
Yes,really.

05:41.800 --> 05:47.610
Although,it is considerate to let your
partner know your plans,so she won't worry.

05:47.620 --> 05:50.230
Sweetie,I'm going out for
a drink with Alan,okay?

05:50.240 --> 05:51.440
Sure! Have fun!

05:51.450 --> 05:54.060
Thanks! Love you!

05:56.830 --> 05:58.720
Shut up.

06:00.640 --> 06:02.250
You're driving.

06:04.780 --> 06:07.110
Jake has one big-ass head.

06:09.760 --> 06:13.190
All kidding aside,she's a great girl and
I'm sure you're going to be very happy.

06:13.200 --> 06:14.450
Thanks.

06:14.700 --> 06:17.190
Forever.

06:18.200 --> 06:19.430
Are you done poking?

06:19.440 --> 06:21.140
For the moment.

06:22.110 --> 06:26.330
Boy,who would've figured that of the two of
us I'd end up being the carefree bachelor?

06:26.340 --> 06:31.070
If by carefree,you mean broke and
lonely,everybody would've figured.

06:36.030 --> 06:36.970
Charlie.

06:36.980 --> 06:38.390
Betsy.

06:38.400 --> 06:40.640
I'm getting married on June 26.

06:40.650 --> 06:42.520
Good for you.

06:42.530 --> 06:43.780
At the Bel Air Hotel.

06:43.790 --> 06:45.490
Nice!

06:47.210 --> 06:51.100
That means no matter how easy
you are,I can't sleep with you.

06:51.780 --> 06:54.000
I can. I'm Alan.

06:55.260 --> 06:57.170
Can he buy you a drink?

07:02.120 --> 07:02.910
What you watching?

07:02.920 --> 07:04.670
Golf!

07:06.410 --> 07:08.270
Don't sneak up on a guy,all right?

07:08.280 --> 07:09.680
Sorry.

07:09.940 --> 07:12.150
Your dad watches a lot of golf,too.

07:13.620 --> 07:17.100
So,listen,how'd you like to
be a groomsman in the wedding?

07:17.110 --> 07:18.290
What do I gotta do?

07:18.300 --> 07:23.430
You just walk down the aisle with one of the
bridesmaids and stand with Charlie during the ceremony.

07:24.020 --> 07:26.280
Tell me more about the bridesmaids.

07:26.290 --> 07:27.870
They're friends of mine.

07:27.880 --> 07:29.960
So,they're old.

07:30.140 --> 07:32.690
No,not all of them.

07:32.700 --> 07:34.290
I have a niece who's about your age.

07:34.300 --> 07:35.130
Is she pretty?

07:35.140 --> 07:36.560
I think she's cute.

07:36.570 --> 07:38.750
Okay,I know what that means.

07:40.630 --> 07:42.240
She's not a brainiac,is she?

07:42.250 --> 07:43.830
What does that mean?

07:43.840 --> 07:47.800
Well,I don't like 'em stupid,but I
don't like 'em talkin' down to me either.

07:47.980 --> 07:49.060
Got it.

07:49.070 --> 07:51.620
And I like a little junk in the trunk.

07:52.290 --> 07:53.900
You won't be disappointed.

07:53.930 --> 07:55.160
All right,I'm in.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.770
Great.

07:58.190 --> 08:01.020
You know,of all the women my
uncle's been with,you're my favorite.

08:01.030 --> 08:02.490
Oh,thank you.

08:02.500 --> 08:04.370
And there's been a lot.

08:04.800 --> 08:05.710
I know.

08:05.740 --> 08:07.680
A whole lot.

08:08.290 --> 08:09.120
Right.

08:09.130 --> 08:11.850
Like,I'm betting around a thousand.

08:14.010 --> 08:17.120
And that's just since I've been
old enough to pay attention.

08:17.570 --> 08:18.370
No kidding.

08:18.380 --> 08:22.860
When I first got here,he told me that
they were coming over to water the plants.

08:23.100 --> 08:25.190
And I believed him.

08:25.230 --> 08:26.870
What did I know?

08:27.680 --> 08:28.970
Sure. You were young.

08:28.980 --> 08:30.040
And naive,too.

08:30.050 --> 08:32.179
We didn't have any plants.

08:33.240 --> 08:35.390
And there were some crazy ones,too.

08:35.400 --> 08:36.840
I'll bet.

08:37.020 --> 08:40.929
Your niece doesn't have a license
to carry a concealed weapon,does she?

08:41.590 --> 08:42.760
No.

08:42.770 --> 08:44.360
Good.

08:44.400 --> 08:47.510
You should've seen where
this one girl hid hers.

08:50.490 --> 09:00.090
Come to find out that what I thought was
a boil on my neck was actually a carbuncle.

09:00.100 --> 09:01.960
Lovely.

09:02.180 --> 09:07.460
Little known fact,uh,carbuncles
are technically in the boil family,

09:07.490 --> 09:10.740
but they take way longer to drain.

09:15.150 --> 09:16.720
Charlie,help me here. I'm dying.

09:16.730 --> 09:18.470
No,you're doing fine.

09:18.480 --> 09:20.960
Tell her about your hemorrhoids.

09:21.130 --> 09:23.240
Please,I'm begging you.

09:23.290 --> 09:24.470
All right.

09:24.500 --> 09:27.740
No sense letting my
superpowers go to waste.

09:29.110 --> 09:34.850
So,Dr. Harper,are we still going to Sun
Valley in your Gulf Stream this weekend?

09:34.880 --> 09:37.400
You own your own trailer?

09:37.420 --> 09:39.910
No,no,no,that's an Airstream.

09:39.940 --> 09:42.150
Dr. Harper has a private jet.

09:42.200 --> 09:43.140
Really?

09:43.180 --> 09:46.180
Oh,yeah. He needs one for his work.

09:47.200 --> 09:48.680
What do you do?

09:48.720 --> 09:52.030
Uh,I am a chiropractor.

09:52.230 --> 09:55.460
A chiropractor without borders.

09:55.500 --> 09:59.340
He travels the world adjusting
the backs of starving children.

09:59.370 --> 10:06.020
Yes,you... you have to be,uh,very careful,um,because
their little bones are very brittle.

10:07.680 --> 10:09.030
You're amazing.

10:09.060 --> 10:11.520
Nah,it's just my job.

10:12.220 --> 10:14.180
You're amazing.

10:14.200 --> 10:15.430
It wasn't tough.

10:15.470 --> 10:17.480
We had her at trailer.

10:18.770 --> 10:21.420
Uh,another round. On him.

