Charlie...

11:00.920 --> 11:02.020
Charlie?!

11:02.060 --> 11:03.480
Go away,Alan.

11:03.520 --> 11:07.380
I really think you need to wake up now.

11:08.350 --> 11:09.990
Chelsea's sleeping.

11:10.020 --> 11:14.000
Perhaps,but not here.

11:14.150 --> 11:18.860
Okay,what the hell is your prob...

11:20.160 --> 11:22.330
Oh,dear.

11:23.670 --> 11:25.200
What happened?

11:25.210 --> 11:27.190
I don't know.

11:27.200 --> 11:28.390
Who is she?

11:28.400 --> 11:31.190
I don't know.

11:31.220 --> 11:32.990
What the helldoyou know,Alan?

11:33.030 --> 11:39.810
I know we're in a strange
woman's bed,together,naked.

11:48.100 --> 11:49.570
Let's get the hell out of here.

11:49.610 --> 11:51.250
Good idea.

11:53.890 --> 11:54.970
Do you rember anything?

11:55.010 --> 11:56.770
Well,I remember we were in Pavlov's.

11:56.800 --> 11:59.870
Oh,yeah,yeah,yeah. You
were hitting on some chick.

11:59.960 --> 12:02.100
Guess it worked.

12:02.360 --> 12:04.600
Do you happen to rember how I did it?

12:04.630 --> 12:05.620
Alan,focus.

12:05.630 --> 12:10.300
Okay,right,right. I-I think there was
something about a-a trailer in Sun Valley.

12:10.310 --> 12:12.650
Are we in Idaho?

12:13.930 --> 12:16.240
No mountains,no snow.

12:18.310 --> 12:21.210
Why are you wearing my underwear?

12:21.300 --> 12:23.240
Why are you wearing mine?

12:23.280 --> 12:25.250
Oh,boy.

12:26.750 --> 12:28.000
Let's just go.

12:28.040 --> 12:30.340
Should we leave her a little note?

12:30.410 --> 12:31.080
What?!

12:31.090 --> 12:33.110
You know,a thank
you,maybe my phone number.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.500
Are you crazy?! Just keep moving!

12:34.510 --> 12:36.660
But she's cute,and I'm gonna
need a plus one for your wedding.

12:36.670 --> 12:38.830
Oh,my God,my wedding.

12:38.840 --> 12:41.010
You're right,it could be awkward.

12:43.930 --> 12:45.700
What have I done,Alan?

12:45.710 --> 12:50.810
Less than 24 hours after I set a date for my
wedding,I wake up in bed with another woman.

12:50.820 --> 12:52.670
And me.

12:52.680 --> 12:55.210
You woke up in bed with me,too.

13:04.840 --> 13:07.060
What the hell did we do last night?

13:07.110 --> 13:08.320
I wish I knew.

13:08.350 --> 13:09.990
What am I gonna tell Chelsea?

13:10.030 --> 13:12.940
Well,let-let's think. I mean,maybe
there's an innocent explanation.

13:12.950 --> 13:14.940
Oh,really? And what might that be?

13:14.950 --> 13:18.250
- Okay,clearly,we all had a bit much to drink.
- Yeah.

13:18.260 --> 13:21.870
And you and I,being
gentlemen,escorted the lady home.

13:22.420 --> 13:24.920
She invited us in for a
cup of coffee to sober up.

13:24.930 --> 13:28.470
Was that before or after
we switched underwear?

13:30.460 --> 13:31.630
Let me finish.

13:31.640 --> 13:36.550
Uh,so,we went into her apartment and...

13:37.370 --> 13:39.730
I don't know what you're
gonna tell Chelsea.

13:39.760 --> 13:41.280
Here is what you tell her.

13:41.310 --> 13:45.850
Tell her you were detained by the secret
police,strip-searched and water-boarded.

13:45.890 --> 13:47.980
Just drive.

13:48.120 --> 13:50.470
Worked for me.

13:53.110 --> 13:54.600
All right.

13:54.610 --> 13:56.400
Here's what we're gonna do.

13:56.410 --> 13:58.640
We're gonna forget this
night ever happened.

13:58.650 --> 14:00.140
Good idea.

14:00.950 --> 14:03.930
Giddy-up
horsey,giddy-up.

14:07.260 --> 14:10.840
Of course,that may be
easier said than done.

14:21.660 --> 14:24.010
Great. No one's up yet.

14:24.020 --> 14:25.160
All right,go to bed.

14:25.170 --> 14:26.900
I'll see you later.

14:31.160 --> 14:32.140
Charlie?

14:32.150 --> 14:32.780
What?

14:32.790 --> 14:34.720
You want your boxers back?

14:36.700 --> 14:37.650
You keep 'em.

14:37.660 --> 14:39.730
Really? Gee,thanks.

14:41.850 --> 14:43.220
Oh,oh,Charlie?! Charlie?

14:43.230 --> 14:43.930
Yeah?

14:43.940 --> 14:47.570
Uh,if I put 'em in the laundry,Berta
will wash them and give them back to you.

14:47.580 --> 14:49.590
Then hand-wash 'em.

14:49.840 --> 14:51.550
Of course.

14:53.640 --> 14:55.000
Charlie?! Charlie?!

14:55.010 --> 14:56.510
What?

14:56.530 --> 14:58.730
Woolite or a mild detergent?

14:58.760 --> 14:59.750
I don't care.

14:59.810 --> 15:02.620
All right,no worries.
I'll check the label.

15:03.800 --> 15:05.500
Oh,Charlie?

15:06.040 --> 15:06.690
What?

15:06.700 --> 15:09.490
Thanks for taking me out with you
tonight. I had a really good time.

15:39.610 --> 15:41.080
Charlie?

15:41.710 --> 15:42.630
Yeah,babe?

15:42.640 --> 15:44.320
Are you just getting home?

15:44.330 --> 15:48.320
No,no... no,I was a little drunk,so
I slept downstairs for a while.

15:48.330 --> 15:49.870
I didn't want to disturb you.

15:49.880 --> 15:51.980
Did you have a good time with Alan?

15:51.990 --> 15:53.390
Oh,come on,it was Alan.

15:53.400 --> 15:55.860
How much fun could I have had?

15:56.350 --> 16:02.930
Happy birthday Mr. President

16:02.970 --> 16:08.810
Happy birthday To you.

16:10.150 --> 16:12.340
Oh,you don't mean that.

16:12.350 --> 16:16.110
No,no. We had an okay time.

16:16.260 --> 16:18.510
Pretty forgettable.

16:19.190 --> 16:21.060
I talked to my parents last night.

16:21.110 --> 16:23.480
They are so excited.

16:23.510 --> 16:26.250
Not as excited as me.

16:29.190 --> 16:32.080
I'm gonna make you a
great wife,Charlie Harper.

16:32.130 --> 16:33.520
I know.

16:33.550 --> 16:39.340
And I'm gonna... cut
down on my drinking.

16:42.470 --> 16:44.280
Boy,I don't know,Chels.

16:44.290 --> 16:47.000
I really like the white
roses for the centerpieces.

16:47.010 --> 16:48.140
You don't think it's too much?

16:48.150 --> 16:57.490
No. No. The rose symbolizes love,and white
symbolizes,you know,the cleanness of that love.

16:58.770 --> 17:00.020
Cleanness?

17:00.030 --> 17:06.030
Yeah,yeah,like purity
or... untainted by filth.

17:07.800 --> 17:10.770
A white rose is a rose you can trust.

17:10.780 --> 17:15.550
And making it the centerpiece is
appropriate because you're mycenterpiece.

17:15.710 --> 17:20.140
You know,the piece that
supercedes all other pieces.

17:21.099 --> 17:22.589
Are you still drunk?

17:22.630 --> 17:24.720
Only with love.

17:26.720 --> 17:28.900
Oh,it's my grandmother.

17:29.540 --> 17:31.350
Hi,Grammy!

17:31.370 --> 17:34.500
Yeah,it's gonna be a June wedding.

17:35.160 --> 17:36.840
Excuse me.

17:36.890 --> 17:39.310
That's a terrible thing to say,Grammy.

17:39.360 --> 17:42.920
Besides,I said "June," not "Jew."

17:52.200 --> 17:55.000
Okay,what've you done?

17:55.030 --> 17:55.840
Beg your pardon?

17:55.880 --> 18:01.640
That sweet,naive hick you're marrying might buy
this loving,cooperative attitude,but not your mommy.

18:01.650 --> 18:04.380
Hey,can't a fella just be
excited about floral centerpieces?

18:04.390 --> 18:06.390
A gay fella.

18:07.510 --> 18:09.850
You're feeling guilty
about something. What is it?

18:09.860 --> 18:13.730
Nothing. I've got nothing
to feel guilty about.

18:15.580 --> 18:20.120
Okay,okay,okay,now you
give him your underwear.

18:21.610 --> 18:22.910
Charlie...

18:22.920 --> 18:24.870
I'm not really sure what I did.

18:24.880 --> 18:26.980
So,a drunken escapade?

18:26.990 --> 18:29.210
Is there another kind of escapade?

18:29.220 --> 18:33.100
Well,whatever you do,don't
tell Chelsea about it.

18:33.110 --> 18:38.860
Confession may be good for the soul,but
it's a hot lead enema to a marriage.

18:39.000 --> 18:44.790
I know,I know,but I've got these freaky
memory flashes,and I feel so guilty.

18:44.830 --> 18:48.910
Trust me... those memories
will fade with time.

18:48.930 --> 18:49.990
How do you know?

18:50.030 --> 18:52.120
Let me tell you a story.

18:52.260 --> 18:55.570
Many years ago,when I was married
to your second stepfather...

18:55.610 --> 18:57.670
The carpet king?

18:57.920 --> 18:59.360
Well,I called him that.

18:59.370 --> 19:01.780
Wasn't his occupation.

19:02.470 --> 19:11.050
Anyway,he was away on business,and you and your
brother were in summer camp or somewhere,and I...

19:11.060 --> 19:17.390
Well,I was lonely,bored
and the circus was in town.

19:18.920 --> 19:26.300
And when I woke up in that Motel 6,clown
makeup smeared all over my bosom,I was alone.

19:26.310 --> 19:30.930
The Chinese acrobats,the strong man and the
little people had moved on to the next town.

19:30.940 --> 19:33.370
Oh,my God!

19:34.360 --> 19:35.620
What did you do then?

19:35.630 --> 19:37.210
Well,what could I do?

19:37.220 --> 19:41.250
I showered,plucked the
sequins from my hoo-hoo...

19:42.060 --> 19:45.100
held my head up,got on with my life.

19:45.120 --> 19:47.350
And you never told the carpet king?

19:47.390 --> 19:49.710
No,of course not.

19:49.750 --> 19:51.700
I loved him too much.

19:51.730 --> 19:55.950
Your second stepfather was the third
best thing that ever happened to me.

19:56.080 --> 19:58.310
Behind me and Alan?

19:58.690 --> 20:00.780
Sure.

20:03.920 --> 20:07.640
I think some teenagers are fooling
around under the deck again.

20:07.650 --> 20:08.800
Really?

20:08.830 --> 20:12.450
Yeah,I found a pair of men's
briefs by the side of the house.

20:12.600 --> 20:14.240
Damn kids.

20:14.260 --> 20:16.450
No respect for anything.

20:22.230 --> 20:26.880
Listen,Chels... we need to talk.

20:26.940 --> 20:28.870
Something wrong?

20:29.160 --> 20:30.920
Yeah.

20:30.990 --> 20:32.540
What is it?

20:32.660 --> 20:36.960
I got these... these
pictures in my head,

20:36.990 --> 20:41.450
and I'm afraid if I don't tell you
about them,they're gonna drive me crazy.

20:41.500 --> 20:43.780
Go ahead.

20:46.130 --> 20:48.990
Well,what happened was...

20:50.440 --> 20:55.030
my second stepfather went on a business
trip while the circus was in town.

20:55.330 --> 21:03.310
Alan and I were at camp-- or
someplace-- and my mother was lonely.

21:24.670 --> 21:25.930
***

